<p>Note that the bindings for <code>ace-select-window</code> and <code>transpose-frame</code> require that you have the <a href="https://melpa.org/#/ace-window">ace-window</a> and <a href="https://melpa.org/#/transpose-frame">transpose-frame</a> packages installed.</p>
<h1>Closing Thoughts</h1>
<p>Registers, rectangles, and managing windows in Emacs are powerful features that are made easier to use with Casual. If you haven’t explored them, consider trying them out. I think you’ll be pleasantly surprised by what they offer and over time will consider them essential to your Emacs experience.</p>